The evidence with the title 'McCain's Misleading Mailer - FactCheck.org ' says Jan 15, 2008  ... It says , "Hillary tried to spend $1 million for a Woodstock museum" until "John McCain said no . "In fact  ... That would have allotted $ 1 million to New York state's Bethel Woods Center For The Arts , the proposed site of a museum celebrating the 1969 Woodstock music festival and its effect on American culture . 
